<h1 id="sdk">eKeynox Mobile SDK</h1>

<% diagram = image_tag("../images/ekeynox_libraries.png", :alt => "Librairies ekeynox", :class => "diagram-r") %> 
<%= link_to diagram, lightbox_mobile_sdk_lb_path, :class => "zoombox h410 w1000" %>

<p>eKeynox Mobile SDK helps you integrate security into your mobile applications easily, whether they be web or native applications. In particular, this SDK gives you an effective way to handle digital certificates and their PKI logic. To get started with development quickly, all you have to do is import eKeynox libraries into your project and follow the eKeynox tutorial.</p>

<p>eKeynox libraries enable you to sign transactions and contracts, handle strong user authentication, and more. The libraries leverage the eKeynox KeyWallet, a software cryptographic engine that includes secure storage as well as a cryptographic API. KeyWallet is compatible with security elements such as microSD, SIM cards, smartcards, and NFC chips, and also gives you a secure software alternative when this type of hardware is not available.</p>

<p>eKeynox Mobile SDK is part of a starter package that includes training, support, and eKeynox management services in SaaS mode for developers. Sample code and documentation are available on <%= link_to 'github eKeynox', "https://github.com/netheos", :target => "_blank" %>.</p>

